  "reasoning": "The quantification of costs is based on a blend of direct context provided (e.g., FDA Warning Letter remediation, percentage of time wasted) and industry-standard assumptions. For 'Time Lost,' a loaded hourly rate of $84.13 (based on an assumed $175,000/year salary) for 5 validation team members, wasting 20-40% of their time, was used to derive the annual dollar value. Regulatory penalties and delayed product launches reflect the severe, albeit less frequent, high-impact events for which the risk must be accounted. Hidden audit costs and consultant fees represent more common, mid-range financial drains. Total Annual Risk aggregates these potential exposures. The price justification directly ties the modest annual cost of the solution ($15,000/year average) to the tangible, recurring savings in time and the catastrophic costs it helps prevent, demonstrating rapid break-even and substantial ROI multiples. The narrative reinforces compliance as a strategic asset rather than a necessary evil."
